  "doc_id": "4683",
  "text": "The frequency with which L. monocytogenes can be found during environmental surveys has raised doubts that food manufacturers can effectively eliminate L. monocytogenes from the workplace. However, investigation of a turkeyprocessing plant associated with a case of human listeriosis yielded encouraging results [CITATION_1] . Listeria contamination of the plant was not widespread; the strain associated with disease was restricted to the peeler used to process turkey franks. Additional industrial studies may improve the ability to identify areas where Listeria clean-up will be most effective.",
